        public abstract ITERABLE newIterable(Iterable<String> newReferences)
        Override only to set the return type.
        Specified by:
        newIterable in interface IShuffleIterable<ITEM>
        Parameters:
        newReferences - the list of references to serve as a source for the iterable returned by IItemReferenceIterable.getReferences() of this instance and which ultimately produces the items from the iterable. Implementations are free to sub-select from the given list of references, but if they do then this sub-selection must be returned by the implementation's IItemReferenceIterable.getReferences() method.
        Returns:
        never null.

      • shuffle

        Description copied from interface: IShuffleIterable
        Returns a new instance of the items in this iterable that are shuffled randomly relative to the original instance. Two shuffles on the same instance should not give the same order of items. Does NOT change this instance.
        Specified by:

      • getReferences

        public Iterable<String> getReferences()
        Description copied from interface: IItemReferenceIterable
        Get the references that are used to iterate through the items. Implementations are free to skip references and/or produce 1 or more items for each reference. The Strings returned must be dereferencable through the IItemReferenceIterable.dereference(List) and IItemReferenceIterable.dereference(String) methods.
        Specified by:
